output:
apt:
  name: teleport
  state: present
input: name: Ensure Teleport is installed in Debian.
starcoder-response:
name: Ensure Teleport is installed in Debian.

Answer: when: ansible_os_family == 'Debian'
block:
- name: Install dependencies (Debian)
  ansible.builtin.apt:
    name:
    - ca-certificates
    - gnupg
    - xz-utils
    state: present
- name: Install Teleport
  ansible.builtin.apt:
    deb: https://get.gravitational.com/teleport-v{{ teleport_version }}-linux-{{ teleport_architecture
      }}.deb
    state: present
    dpkg_options: force-confnew,force-confdef
    autoclean: true
    autoremove: true
    update_cache: true
    cache_valid_time: 3600
  vars:
    teleport_bin_name: teleport
- name: Create {{ teleport_install_dir }}/bin symlink to teleport
  ansible.builtin.file:
    src: /teleport
    dest: /usr/local/bin/teleport
    state: link
    force: true
  when: not teleport_bin_symlink_created
- name: Run teleport init
  ansible.builtin.command:
    cmd: /teleport init
    creates: /teleport_install_dir/bin/teleport
  when: not teleport_bin_symlink_created
- name: Grant root access to teleport config
  ansible.builtin.file:
    path: /etc/teleport.yaml
    owner: root
    group: root
    mode: 384
    state: file
  when: not teleport_config_file.stat.exists
- name: Generate default config for teleport
  ansible.builtin.template:
    src: default_teleport.yaml.j2
    dest: /etc/teleport.yaml
    owner: root
    group: root
    mode: 384
  when: not teleport_config_file.stat.exists
- name: Reload systemd daemon
  ansible.builtin.systemd:
    daemon_reload: true
  when: teleport_bin_symlink_created.changed
- name: Reboot the node to apply configuration changes
  ansible.builtin.reboot: null
when: teleport_install_dir is defined

  ansible.builtin.apt:
    name:
    - automake

    - libncurses5-dev
    - make
    - pkg-config

  ansible.builtin.yum:
    name:
    - automake
    - byacc
    - gcc
    - git
    - libevent-devel
    - ncurses-devel
    - xclip
    - xsel
    state: installed
  when: ansible_pkg_mgr == 'yum' or ansible_pkg_mgr == 'dnf'
- name: Git cloning tmux source
  ansible.builtin.git:
    repo: https://github.com/tmux/tmux.git
    dest: /usr/src/tmux
    version: 3.3a
- name: Running autogen.sh
  ansible.builtin.command: /bin/sh autogen.sh
  args:
    chdir: /usr/src/tmux
    creates: /usr/src/tmux/configure
- name: Running ./configure
  ansible.builtin.command: ./configure
  args:
    chdir: /usr/src/tmux
    creates: Makefile
- name: Running make
  community.general.make:
    chdir: /usr/src/tmux
    params:
      NUMTHREADS: 4
- name: Installing via make install
  community.general.make:
    chdir: /usr/src/tmux
    target: install
- name: Adding /usr/local/bin to PATH via /etc/profile.d/tmux.sh
  ansible.builtin.copy:
    src: tmux.sh
    dest: /etc/profile.d/tmux.sh
    mode: '0644'
  when: ansible_os_family == 'RedHat'

  file:

block:
- name: Install kubernetes-cni
  ansible.builtin.apt:
    name: kubernetes-cni
    state: present
    update_cache: true
- name: Install kubeadm
  ansible.builtin.apt:
    name: kubeadm
    state: present
    update_cache: true
    cache_valid_time: 3600
- name: Create kubelet systemd unit
  ansible.builtin.template:
    src: kubelet.service.j2
    dest: /etc/systemd/system/kubelet.service
    mode: '0644'
  register: kubelet_unitfile_created
- name: Enable kubelet systemd unit
  ansible.builtin.systemd:
    name: kubelet
    enabled: true
  when:
    - kubelet_unitfile_created is changed
- name: Check if kubeadm is installed
  ansible.builtin.stat:
    path: /opt/kubernetes/bin/kubeadm
  register: kubeadm_bin
- name: Install kubeadm
  ansible.builtin.get_url:
    url: https://dl.k8s.io/release/v1.19.3/bin/linux/amd64/kubeadm
    dest: /opt/kubernetes/bin/kubeadm
    mode: '0755'
    force: true
  when:
  - kubeadm_bin is not defined
- name: Create kubeadm symlink
  ansible.builtin.file:
    src: /opt/kubernetes/bin/kubeadm
    dest: /usr/bin/kubeadm
    owner: root
    group: root
    state: link
    force: true
  when:

- name: Print kubectl installation status

  when:
  - kubectl_install_status.stat.exists
